A CATTLE herder and his unknown male friend died in a mysterious fire that engulfed the garage where they were sleeping.The incident happened at about 2am at Half Rolle Village outside Thulamahashe near Bushbuckridge, Mpumalanga yesterday. Mzondwana Mathebula (55) and his friend, whose identity is not yet known, were burned beyond recognition.The dead man was hired by Tom Mgiba’s family to herd cattle. Villagers tried to save the men but the flames were too strong. Asser Mgiba said it took them almost three hours to put out the fire as they only had buckets to carry water. “There was nothing we could do. The fire was too strong.”if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjssPfkDPUqA__x_YGjaE-s4KE0cf3MLc77NQ8zy8fpr5nyDw0OmPk2STSPJHAiIx7pQfjGvv7yyp4t46boDBBy1BC17sIqI33ZQipc6Ciegt157wpCqzGuXH42A5U2HRdMH3vQyaV0MTGfAZjG8hV0EuAMvQqlP3kyKE54dWnTFmuNtsa5Ab_pXJAgkXoHqQ3RwIBwTwOxtObeVnJBgJxO3ObyfctLEq1YRq08dIwf8Ph6DD0WLY5LAvmUoT0D3D-YBJ5Ge1BypBUeu7rYUr7HoKFF2C1ak\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzA8LsJ6vRaw4EAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
